<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-564] KMeansClusterer does not use distanceThreshold parameter in testConvergence(Iterable&lt;Cluster&gt; clusters, double distanceThreshold) method</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-564</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While running KMeansClusterer#runKMeansIteration sequentially I noticed that the distanceThreshold parameter is not used. The convergenceDelta field is used instead. However, it&apos;s initialized at 0 and only set when creating a KMeansClusterer with a Configuration object, which is only used in a MapReduce setting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
