                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12970624" author="frankscholten" created="Sun, 12 Dec 2010 18:25:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adds a computeConvergence method to KMeansClusterer which does use the distanceThreshold. Includes unit test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970630" author="ssc" created="Sun, 12 Dec 2010 19:10:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Frank, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;your patch looks good, but it reorders imports and introduces star imports, could you fix that? I guess you&apos;re using IntelliJ which does this automatically (I had the same problem some time ago...).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12970631" author="frankscholten" created="Sun, 12 Dec 2010 19:28:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed reordered imports and star imports&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12979450" author="srowen" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2011 01:28:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m cleaning house on some issues that have stalled &amp;#8211; this look ready-ish to commit.&lt;br/&gt;
But I get an error in the test when I apply it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.AssertionError: Cluster 1 test 3 expected:&amp;lt;4&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;5&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.fail(Assert.java:91)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.failNotEquals(Assert.java:645)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.assertEquals(Assert.java:126)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.assertEquals(Assert.java:470)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.mahout.clustering.kmeans.TestKmeansClustering.testReferenceImplementation(TestKmeansClustering.java:150)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ideas?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12979572" author="srowen" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2011 13:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is due to the fact that the patch changed another test method to use a different threshold, and changing it back works. Frank do you know if that change from 0.001 to 1.5 in the test class was unintentional?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like to do a bit more with this patch. KMeansClusterer was indeed slightly confused since it is in some  cases initialized from a Configuration and sometimes not. In the former case it is supposed to get its threshold internally but in the other case it isn&apos;t, and there was a problem there. Might be more straightforward to have one approach, so I did that locally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12979603" author="frankscholten" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2011 15:25:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, sorry, that threshold change to 1.5 was indeed unintentional.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12979702" author="hudson" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2011 19:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #547 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/547/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/547/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
